cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.FL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new type theory with a specification logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents a new programming language with a rich specification logic. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic) is relevant as the paper deals with clock variables and synchronous functions. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with recursive functions and productive (co)programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents a new language that can be used to develop semantics of other languages and logics.
